<item>
            <title>[LU-17143] Use migrate_copy_data() for all data movement</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17143</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs mirror resync&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; code is using its own implementation of data copying instead of &lt;tt&gt;migrate_copy_data()&lt;/tt&gt;, which means that bug fixes and improvements to the data copying code (eg. bandwidth limit, stats reporting, buffer sizing, DIO usage, etc.) need to be implemented in two places. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be better to have a single function to copy file data shared between the different operations.  &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="78092">LU-17143</key>
            <summary>Use migrate_copy_data() for all data movement</summary>
